name: es6/Notification.js
es6/Observable.js
Observable
description:
A representation of any set of values over any amount of time. This the most basic building block
of RxJS.

params.name: subscribe
params.description:
the function that is
called when the Observable is initially subscribed to. This function is given a Subscriber, to which new values
can be `next`ed, or an `error` method can be called to raise an error, or `complete` can be called to notify
of a succesful completion.

unknown.tagValue: {Observable} a new observable with the Operator applied

creates a new Observable, with this Observable as the source, and the passed
operator defined as the new observable's operator.

params.name: the
params.description: operator defining the operation to take on the observable

return.description: a new observable with the Operator applied

unknown.tagValue: {Subscription} a subscription reference to the registered handlers

registers handlers for handling emitted values, error and completions from the observable, and
 executes the observable's subscriber function, which will take action to set up the underlying data stream

params.name: observerOrNext
params.description:
(optional) either an observer defining all functions to be called,
 or the first of three possible handlers, which is the handler for each value emitted from the observable.

params.name: error
params.description:
(optional) a handler for a terminal event resulting from an error. If no error handler is provided,
 the error will be thrown as unhandled

params.name: complete
params.description: (optional) a handler for a terminal event resulting from successful completion.

return.description: a subscription reference to the registered handlers

unknown.tagValue:
{Promise} a promise that either resolves on observable completion or
 rejects with the handled error

params.name: next
params.description: a handler for each value emitted by the observable

return.description:
a promise that either resolves on observable completion or
 rejects with the handled error

es6/operators/buffer.js
buffer
description:
buffers the incoming observable values until the passed `closingNotifier` emits a value, at which point
it emits the buffer on the returned observable and starts a new buffer internally, awaiting the
next time `closingNotifier` emits

unknown.tagValue: {Observable<T[]>} an observable of buffers, which are arrays of values

params.name: closingNotifier
params.description: an observable, that signals the buffer to be emitted from the returned observable

return.description: an observable of buffers, which are arrays of values

filter
description:
Similar to the well-known `Array.prototype.filter` method, this operator filters values down to a set
allowed by a `select` function

unknown.tagValue: {Observable} an observable of values allowed by the select function

params.name: select
params.description:
a function that is used to select the resulting values
 if it returns `true`, the value is emitted, if `false` the value is not passed to the resulting observable

params.name: thisArg
params.description: an optional argument to determine the value of `this` in the `select` function

return.description: an observable of values allowed by the select function
